關稅估價研究：論國際機制在我國之實施與檢視














出版年:
-


研究生:
嚴嘉美


學號:



論文名稱:
關稅估價研究：論國際機制在我國之實施與檢視


指導教授:
林廷機 Tingji Lin


學位類別:
碩士


校院名稱:
逢甲大學


系所名稱:
公共政策所


學年度:
93


語文別:
中文


論文頁數:
357


開放範圍:
網際網路


中文關鍵字:
世界貿易組織 ，直接效力 ，世界關務組織 ，關稅估價 ，爭端解決


英文關鍵字:
Customs Valuation ，Dispute Settlement ，Direct Effect ，World Customs Organization ，World Trade Organization





[摘要]


本論文（以下稱本文或本研究）旨在探究關稅估價（Customs Valuation）制度之理論基礎、實務運作以及其他相關問題。
                稅收是支持國家體系運作的必要條件，海關則基於國家主權所賦予的權力徵收關稅。
                關稅之稽徵，以從價稅（Ad Valorem Duty）為最主要的課徵方式。一個「合理」且「不專斷」的「估價制度」乃勢所必需，否則GATT╱WTO之關稅減讓及關稅拘束之效果將失其功能。因此，一套眾所咸遵之國際機制（international regime）可降低國際貿易之交易成本和不確定性，並有助於息紛止爭。從而「世界關務組織」之關稅估價制度被吸納成WTO規範。
                爰此，我國採「轉化」方式，經國內立法程序，於「關稅法」及「關稅法施行細則」中，將國際機制中之法律規範接納為國內法，而受國際法之拘束。
                經本文檢視結果，我國「關稅估價」相關規範，歷經數次修正後，就關稅估價規範之內涵，已與國際規範「合轍合軌」。
                至於我國目前已發生關於關稅估價之行政訴訟案例，亦只有法律適用問題，迄無與WTO規範不符之爭端。
                最後，本文展望「虛擬納稅人（Virtual Taxpayer）」議題。際此全球化時代，跨國境、跨區域流通之國際企業日趨興盛重要。彼等採「移轉定價」（transfer pricing）等非常規交易方法，以及利用避稅天堂之類的減免手段，使得其有納稅之實質能力卻讓民族國家政府無從掌握稅收，致使當代各國家之體系維持產生危機。本文認為，貿易只要落實至有體物（及附著其上之智慧財產權等權利）勢必得通過海關管制；交易只要落實至「價格」必有「憑證」、「帳表」或各式「資訊」可循。因此，「關稅估價」及「海關事後稽核」（customs audit）如能確實掌握「價格」，再透過與內地稅相互勾稽，則虛擬納稅人之不實、不當報價與非常規交易勢將無所頓逃。
                另外，本文建議，海關之「分類估價關員」（import specialist）應宏觀全球，並具備與業務攸關之國際商務與經濟法知識，諸如：WTO規範及INCOTERM等貿易條件之類的國際慣例等等，庶幾恪盡職守。



Review on Customs Valuation :The Implementation of International Regime in Taiwan
                Student: Chai-May Yan Advisor: Tingji Lin, Chairman and Associate Professor of Law
                Feng Chia University
                Graduate Institute of Public Policy
                Thesis
                Abstract
                This thesis aims to survey the rationale, the operation of pragmatism and its related concerns on the system of customs valuation.
                Public finance is the prerequisite for the operation to the government, while customs is empowered under the mechanism of the government to collect tariff.
                With regard to the collecting of tariff, Ad Valorem Duty is the vital means. A “reasonable” and “non-arbitrary or non-fictitious” customs valuation system is bound to bring about, or the tariff reduction and bounded effect of GATT/WTO would not make a full play. A set of widely acknowledged international regime could reduce the cost of transaction and the risk of uncertainty on the international trade whereas the conflicts are being eased up along the line accordingly. As a result, the customs valuation of “World Customs Organizational” has been adopted by WTO regulations.
                Consequently, by means of national legislative procedures we have transferred laws of international regime into national laws while governed by the international ones regarding “ Tariff Law” and “Regulations of Tariff Law.”
                As far as this paper is concerned, after continuous modification on our “customs valuation” rules gave been correspondent with the international ones.
                Up to now, there is no administrative lawsuit of customs valuation conflicting with WTO regulations on issue of law applicability.
                Lastly, this paper takes a view of “virtual taxpayer”. In a great era of globalization, international enterprises are increasingly of great importance. Those who are capable of paying tax use such unconventional means as “ transfer pricing” and “tax heaven” and the like to evade tax. As a result, the government could not collect their tax effectively and the operation of national system is also in face of crisis. This paper considers that trade in terms of tangible article ( and its intellectual property rights incurred) should be governed by the customs; while transaction in terms of price should be equipped with “receipt’, “account ” or other related “documentation”. If “customs valuation” and “customs audit” take great advantage of “pricing” with the help of mutual audit through local tax, unconventional transactions , therefore, by “ virtual taxpayers” would not evade audit and supervision.
                In addition, this paper recommends that “ import specialist” should have a good command of related international commerce and economic laws, such as international terms and conditions regulated by WTO and INCOTERM with which they should strictly comply.



[ 論文目次 ]


